reviews.title: A great combo tour of things to do at night
reviews.text: Miguel was my guide and he basically served as a chaperone and facilitator to rendezvous with Aymen the Driver; I wish he would've been a little bit more proactive in telling me information about the area, I had to continuously ask him questions to get him to talk about things. That is why I am only giving it four stars. However, he was very nice and friendly.But.... Aymen was a delight, extremely knowledgeable, and had top-notch driving skills. He really understood how to make a guest feel welcome and not have any stress over the logistics of the tour with its many stops.I was leaving on a flight the next morning so I asked them if instead of three Pisco sours I could get a little food instead and they did accommodate.

reviews.title: A great way to see nightlife in Lima, conveniently and safely
reviews.text: This night tour starts as the sun goes down. Get ready for a wonderful adventure as you go downtown to try the original pisco sour where it was invented. Then enjoy a park with so many magical musical fountains it will make your head spin! The massive central fountain features a projected animated history of Peru set to inspiring music. It must be seen to be believed. Then head out to Barranco for a few more super interesting places for drinks and atmosphere. Having a private guide and driver made life so much easier and more accessible. My guide was Aymen, and he was fantastic. He explained a lot about the history of the drinks, the various districts of Lima, the fountains, and more. He went above and beyond to make sure I had an excellent time, making this one of the most enjoyable parts of my wonderful trip to Peru.
